.Im MicroEmacs macro;function;misc|registry
.so me.tni
.TH &reg 4
.XI &reg - "Retrieve a registry value (with default)"
.SH NAME
&reg \- Retrieve a registry value (with default)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.B &reg
.I root
.I default
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B &reg
retrieves the value of a node defined by \fIroot\fR from the registry, this is
an absolute path.
.PP
The  \fIdefault\fR  value is the  value of the node to return if the  registry
node does not exist.
.SH EXAMPLE
The  following  example is taken from  \fCme.emf\fR  and uses the  registry to
retrieve some of the default configuration files:
.Me $emf-scheme
.CS
; Load in the color setup
!force execute-file &reg &spr "/history/%s/color" $platform "color"
; execute company setup
!if &not &seq &set #l0 &reg "/history/company" ""
    !force execute-file #l0
!endif
.CE 0
.Me $ehf-scheme
